quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,But for him who fears the station of his Lord are gardens twain
  55,47,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,48,Both furnished with branching trees
  55,49,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,50,In each are flowing springs
  55,51,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,52,"In each are, of every fruit, two kinds"
  55,53,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,54,"Reclining on beds the linings of which are of brocade, and the fruit of the two gardens within reach to cull"
  55,55,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,56,Therein are maids of modest glances whom no man nor ginn has deflowered before
  55,57,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,58,As though they were rubies and pearls
  55,59,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,60,Is the reward of goodness aught but goodness
  55,61,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,62,"And besides these, are gardens twain"
  55,63,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,64,With dark green foliage
  55,65,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,66,In each two gushing springs
  55,67,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,68,In each fruit and palms and pomegranates
  55,69,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,70,In them maidens best and fairest
  55,71,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,72,Bright and large-eyed maids kept in their tents
  55,73,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,74,Whom no man nor ginn has deflowered before them
  55,75,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and beautiful carpets
  55,77,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,78,Blessed be the name of thy Lord possessed of majesty and honour